                    <span>The film, although not filled with exciting plot twists, is rather good. Instead of focusing on plot, the film focuses more on character development, as well as the development of a relationship. I believe that we all can relate to situations in which we become friends with someone, yet never keep in touch after this seemingly wonderful time has passed. The characters are real, and heartfelt, and although, like I said, it wasn't incredibly exciting, it does contemplate the mechanics of relationships in a way I never thought possible.</span>
                  
              
